Apply only when producing a plan; ignore in Agent mode.

Use this template (no narrative/background prose):

`**Goal:** <1 sentence>`
`**Files to change:**`
`- <action>: \`path/to/file\` — <what and why, 5-10 words>`
`**Changes:**`
`- <short bullet per logical change; grouped by area>`
`**Acceptance criteria:**`
`- <measurable proof of correctness>`

Rules:
- Use bullets/tables, not paragraphs.
- Keep under ~40 bullets; split into numbered phases if larger.
- Keep technical terms/flags/job names in English; other text may follow user language.
- Do not repeat existing task/file context; cite file paths instead.
- Do not explain tool basics unless explicitly asked.
- Acceptance criteria are mandatory.
- Follow `clarification-first.mdc`; ask clarifying questions if unresolved choices affect the plan.
- For CI/pipeline changes, specify exact `rules:`, `needs:`, and `stage:` per job.
- If multiple viable approaches have meaningful trade-offs, provide a short table (Approach/Pros/Cons) and ask user to choose before detailed planning.

Avoid:
- long context/background restatements;
- duplicated requirements across sections;
- implementation-level file content details in plan mode;
- Mermaid for simple linear flows (use only when branching/parallelism is hard to express with bullets).
